[SN]TITLE[SN]
Milton Keynes flat fire death: Man charged with murder

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with murder after a death in a flat fire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The body of Ashley Gillard, 31, was found at Trevithick Court, Wolverton in Milton Keynes in June.
Thomas White, 26, of Bibury Close, Wellingborough, who was charged in June with arson with intent to endanger life, has now been charged with murder.
Mr White appeared earlier at Aylesbury Crown Court sitting at Amersham and was remanded to appear at Luton Crown Court on 4 January.
He also faces three counts of theft; two of taking a conveyance without authority; one count of fraud; one count of arson in connection with an incident on 8 June in which a Peugeot vehicle was damaged and two counts of possessing drugs.
